item.title: The Proud Tree Fairy Tale for Kids & Teens
item.description:
Welcome to the SweetDream bedtime podcast for kids. With a mix of timeless fairy tales and original stories join us every night for a touch of bedtime magic as our episodes are filled with extraordinary adventures, magical realms, and lovable characters that will send your child to sleep. So get cozy, close your eyes, and let your imagination wander as we dive into a world of bedtime wonders. Sweet Dreams!!!

Hosted on Acast. See acast... Feed: https://feeds.acast.com/public/shows/6636925f5c72f30012addf8f

item.title: Pedro Martin’s (unpacking) Mexikid
item.description: “She asked, ‘do you go by Peter or Pedro? You're writing a memoir - shouldn't, you know?’ I'm writing a story about myself and I don't know myself — so I'm going to take the journey with the character.” ” Pedro Martín is creator of MEXIKID, a graphic memoir about Pedro’s Mexican-American childhood and family in the 1970s - specifically a road trip to Mexico to their legendary abuelito - who may or may not have been part of the Mexican revolution... Feed: https://feeds.megaphone.fm/WIZD2270371687
